resistance coalition said sunday he has agreed to meet hun sen 
prime minister of cambodias vietnamesebacked government 
in a statement released from his residence in beijing sihanouk 
said he had been informed by a french diplomat that hun sen was 
ready to make two concessions in regard to the problem in 
cambodia he did not reveal the nature of the concessions 
he said the meeting of cambodias four warring factions could 
take place as early as may 2 in indonesia or in september in france 
last month hun sen sent a letter to sihanouk saying there are 
elements that show that a fundamental agreement is possible 
between the government and resistance groups 
vietnam invaded cambodia in december 1978 drove out the radical 
khmer rouge regime that defeated the usbacked government in the 
spring of 1975 and installed another communist administration 
hundreds of thousands of cambodians were killed during the 
nearly three years the khmer rouge was in power as it purged 
opponents and drove people out of the cities to impose a harsh form 
of agrarian communism 
prince sihanouk who was deposed in 1970 now leads a resistance 
alliance of his supporters the khmer rouge and cambodians loyal to 
anticommunist son san 
the three alliance members met in march in beijing and formed a 
national defense council which they said would unify their 
guerrilla forces 
hun sen criticized the council saying it was part of a khmer 
rouge plot to regain power 
on sunday radio broadcasts by the resistance coalition denied 
that allegation and said the khmer rouge would not seek exclusive 
control of the future government and the council would not allow 
any faction to harm the others by force 
representatives of the resistance groups and cambodian 
government met in february in indonesia 
the meeting ended without results when no agreement could be 
reached on the formation of a transitional government to be 
established following a withdrawl of the vietnamese troops from 
cambodia they also disagreed on how to monitor the vietnamese 
withdrawal 
an estimated 70000 vietnamese military personnel are in 
cambodia vietnam has said it will withdraw its troops by september 
if the cambodian factions can agree on a political solution 
