divers pulled seven bodies from a murky 
rainswollen river sunday where at least that many people died when 
a 50yearold us highway bridge collapsed 
the search for more victims continued but was hampered by bridge 
debris and muddy waters said state highway patrol lt larry 
durham the cause of the collapse was unknown 
searchers did not know how many victims might be in the river 
said leroy bledsoe team director for nine divers working at the 
site 
