and do some soundings and well just have to go from there he 
said 
state bridge inspectors plan to meet monday morning with the 
national transportation safety board according to covington fire 
chief jerry craig 
the river is slightly swollen from heavy rainfall last month 
craig said 
weve had an unusual amount of rainfall last month the river 
is out of its banks and theres backwater all over the place but 
this happens twice a year every year and has for the past 100 
years craig said 
the river is actually just barely out of its banks we dont 
feel it had any bearing on the collapse said craig 
the highway patrol closed the southbound roadway shortly after 
